race.comment: TRIPLE SPIRIT (7) is a gelding by Yes Yes Yes on debut for the Anthony & Sam Freedman yard. He's drawn ideally in barrier two having won a Cranbourne jumpout leading in. Have to respect the top yard in what looks a winnable race. RUSSIAN INTO IT (4) ran a good race on debut at Cranbourne, no match for a dominant winner there but sticking on well for third. He'll be better for that and this looks a tad easier. RIVER WOLF (16) resumes having run sixth on debut at Kyneton behind a handy horse in Albertville. He can be an improver this time around. BOLD AMORE (3) ran well fresh and is in the mix.
